Q. Did he say any thing more to you? - A. No;
Jacob Isgar
said to him, one time particularly, that was the man that wrote the dead man's name; Austin's answer was, no, I could not do it, for you wrote one letter yourself.

Q. Did you ever find the hogshead afterwards? - A. Yes;
William Norris
found it.

On the 13th of April, two of my apprentices informed me they saw the prisoners, Maddy and Brown roll a hogshead away; I acquainted Mr. May, Mrs. Rogers's foreman of it, the next morning, he looked over the casks and missed one; I saw a hogshead that corresponded with two I saw in the warehouse, the next evening, in a yard, belonging to Mr. Mathews, in Bunhill-row; I looked at the hogshead, and saw it was the same mark with those I saw at Mrs. Rogers's;
William Norris
was with me, Josiah did not go, he was very busy, and May was present with me.
